and “other” are omitted as surplus. In subclause (A), the words “procure, contract for, or otherwise” are omitted as surplus. The words “for itself or in carrying out an arrangement under which payment is made by the Government or payment is made from amounts provided for the use of the Government” are substituted for “in furtherance of the purposes or pursuant to the terms of any contract, agreement, or other special arrangement made or entered into under which payment is made by the United States or payment is made from funds appropriated, owned, controlled, granted, or conditionally granted or utilized by or otherwise” for clarity and to eliminate unnecessary words. In subclause (B), the word “country” is substituted for “nation” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the Code. The words “international or other organization” are substituted for “international agency, or other organization, of whatever nationality” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “provisions for” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), before clause (1), the words “government of a foreign country” are substituted for “foreign government” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the Code. The words “or governments” are omitted because of 1:1.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “for payment for personnel or cargo transportation” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d), the words “the limitations established by” are omitted as surplus. The words “after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-07"},"text":"October 7, 1978","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as executed. The words “Secretary of State” are substituted for “Department of State” because of 22:2651. The words “Director of the United States Information Agency” are substituted for “International Communication Agency” in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1978-10-07/s706"},"text":"section 706 of the Act of October 7, 1978","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/426"},"text":"Public Law 95–426","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/992"},"text":"92 Stat. 992","children":[],"tail":"), because of section 2 of Reorganization Plan No. 2 of 1977 (eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1636"},"text":"91 Stat. 1636","children":[],"tail":") and section 303(b) of the United States Information Agency Authorization Act, Fiscals Year 1982 and 1983 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/241"},"text":"Public Law 97–241","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/291"},"text":"96 Stat. 291","children":[],"tail":"). The words “Director of the United States International Development Cooperation Agency” are substituted for “Agency for International Development (or any successor agency)” in section 706 because of section 6(a)(3) of Reorganization Plan No. 2 of 1979 (eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/1379"},"text":"93 Stat. 1379","children":[],"tail":"). The words “a foreign air carrier” are substituted for “air carriers which do not hold certificates under section 1371 of this Appendix” for clarity. See H. Conf. Rept. No. 95–1535, 95th Cong., 2d Sess., p. 45 (1978)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the word “affect” is substituted for “prevent” for clarity. The words “to such traffic” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idcbaf47e2-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287/s5/68/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287, § 5(68)(A)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This amends the catchline for 49:40118(d) to make a clarifying amendment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idcbaf47e3-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287/s5/68/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287, § 5(68)(B)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This amends 49:40118(f)(1) to make a clarifying amendment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcbaf47e4-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcbaf47e5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—Subsecs. (c), (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s377/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 377(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), added subsec. (c) and redesignated former subsec. (c) as (d). Former subsec. (d) redesignated (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s377/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 377(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated subsec. (d) as (e) and substituted “subsections (a) and (d)” for “subsections (a) and (c)”. Former subsec. (e) redesignated (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (f) to (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s377/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 377(1)","chil